{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "2eb22e62-f949-4d50-bd49-9d3eb7382a3f",
    "name": "Incident Tracking System API",
    "description": "This Postman Collection contains all the API endpoints for the **Incident Management System**, which is designed to track and manage incidents, services, and users within an organization. The system supports role-based access for **Admin**, **Engineer**, and **User** roles and provides features such as incident reporting, assignment, updates, history tracking, and priority escalation.\n\n#### **Features Covered:**\n\n- **User Authentication & Authorization**\n    \n    - Register, login, and JWT-based authentication.\n        \n    - Role-based access control (Admin / Engineer / User).\n        \n- **Incident Management**\n    \n    - Report new incidents.\n        \n    - Assign incidents to engineers (Admin only).\n        \n    - Update incident status (Engineer).\n        \n    - View incident history.\n        \n    - Fetch all incidents or user-specific incidents.\n        \n- **Services Management**\n    \n    - List of services for which incidents can be reported.\n        \n    - Fetch service details.\n        \n- **Priority & Escalation**\n    \n    - Automatically calculate priority based on impact and urgency.\n        \n    - Escalate incidents using cron-based automation (backend logic).\n        \n- **Real time update (Optional)**\n    \n    - System send real time incident reported by user",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "52905966",
    "_collection_link": "https://go.postman.co/collection/52905966-2eb22e62-f949-4d50-bd49-9d3eb7382a3f?source=collection_link"
  },
